Content structure Clyde focuses on good, readable, responsive documentation. It’s side bar indexes in only 2 levels. It’s opinionated, because deeply nested manuals are hard to follow and takes much too long to navigate.
{divider}  Files     ├── content│ ├── category folder│ │ ├── sub-category folder│ │ │ └──_index.md│ │ └── _index.md│ ├── another category |      The code snippet is pulled from this page

Sidebar category indexing Clyde indexes the first level of the sidebar manu by looking for type: product.
By default, we use feather icons, and the icon renders as specified by icon: "icon-layers"
The example provided is consistent with this example project.

Sidebar sub-category indexing Clyde indexes the second level of the sidebar manu by looking for type: docs.
The layout: two-col specifies the layout of the document.
There is also the layout: single-col for a single column layout.
The ordering of the menu items can be found from weight: 1
